Direct the Office of the Municipal Accountant to conduct a thorough analysis on the receivable accounts to include determination whether the claims were impaired or not and to set up the corresponding allowance for impairment, if there is any;
Record the necessary adjusting and/or correcting entries if circumstances warrant as a result of the thorough analysis;
Present the necessary disclosures in the Notes to Financial Statements as required under Paragraph 30 of IPSAS 30; and
The concerned office review the existing Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) of the loans granted to individual and establish a policy to enforce collectability if not provided therein.

Recommendations:
We recommended the following:
The Municipal Accountant in coordination with the Office of the Municipal Engineer retrieve the certificates of completion of all items of PPE where no depreciation expense was provided;
After the retrieval of certificates of completion, the Municipal Accountant compute the corresponding depreciation expense and record the adjustment by drawing a journal entry voucher;
The Municipal Accountant prepare and maintain the required Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Card (PPELC); and
Institution of possible sanctions for failure to comply with the requirements under the applicable rules and regulations.

Recommendations:
We recommended the following:
The Municipal Treasurer update the stock card by recording all issuances of supplies as reflected in the Requisition and Issue Slip (RIS);
The Municipal Accountant maintain the required supplies ledger to facilitate the necessary reconciliation between the stock card;
Creation of an Inventory Committee to undertake the physical count of inventory items semestrally and accomplish the required Report of the Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) thereafter and submit the same to the auditor concerned not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively; and
Imposition of sanction on the part of accountable person for failure to comply with the requirements.

a) Post the utilization report of the SEF Budget in the website of the LGU and/or in at least three (3) conspicuous public places for transparency and accountability in compliance with the Full Disclosure Policy of the DILG; 

b) Furnish COA with copies of the Quarterly and Annual Reports of SEF Utilization, as prepared by the Local Accountant, received by DepEd, the local sanggunian concerned and Regional Offices of the DBM and DILG; and 

c) In the preparation of the Local School Board Budget, the members of the Local School Board give priority to programs, activities and projects based in the DepEd-approved SIP and DEDP in the implementation of the ECCD Program, kindergarten, elementary and secondary, formal and non-formal education programs and utilize the same to such purpose prescribed by law for which the SEF was created.

We recommend to Management the following:

1.	Direct the MPDC and Municipal Engineer to judiciously prepare and submit project documents to expedite fund releases and implementation and completion of PAMANA projects;

2.	The BAC should fast-track the procurement process in consonance with the earliest mandated time prescribed in the IRR of RA 9184;

3.	Direct the MPDC and Municipal Engineer to constantly monitor project implementation to ensure that projects were implemented in accordance with the government standards and MOA; and

4.	Direct the MPDC, Municipal Engineer and Municipal Accountant to regularly prepare and submit SORD and liquidation documents to DAR to ensure prompt release of subsequent tranches and reconcile both accounting records.

